properties.name: Albuquerque, New Mexico
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Albequerque, NMBig city with lots to do, The worlds highest tram is here. I rode on it and i think it takes you by suspended cable car 14,000 feet up to a mountain top restaurant. Awesome.

properties.name: Detroit, Michigan in January
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27DetroitAt the beginning of every year Detroit hosts the NAIAS(North American International Auto Show). I\'ve always been big into cars and technology, and this is arguably the biggest and most important auto show where every automaker unveils their vehicles, concept cars, and future ideas. If you\'re into cars, it\'s definately something to do in your lifetime.

properties.name: LA/Hollywood
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Hollywood, CAHollywood is really worth visiting, The walk of fame, the production studios, the shopping. I mean come on. It\'s Hollywood. Not to mention Disney Land, Universal Studios, and much much more.

properties.name: Mardi Gras
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27New Orleans, LAPretty Obvious. Mardis Gras is Mardis Gras.

properties.name: Nopi Nationals
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Atlanta, GALike i said about Detroit, i\'m really into cars. So the best place in the country for everything custom car, truck, and bike can be found right by atlanta at NOPI Nationals. The biggest custom car show in the states. Car shows, drag racing, drifting, nightlife, bikini contests, wet t contests... and so on.

properties.name: Orlando, FL
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Orlando, FLPretty Much a non-stop week of fun. Every Theme Park imaginable, plus sea-world. Great eating. Awesome place to go with friends or family, and one of the most popular Vacation spots in the US.

properties.name: Our Nation's Capital
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Washington D.CD.C. has the white house, the pentagon, and everying you could imagine. There are also alot of Museums and stuff like the Smithsonian. Even if you don\'t care too much about stuff like this, it would still be pretty awesome!

properties.name: PCB Spring Break
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Panama City BeachIt\'s pretty much self explanatory, but it\'s pretty much a weeklong party with thousands of college kids, it\'s the original site of MTV spring break, and they continue to visit every year. There\'s everything from laying on the beach, to beach dance clubs, to wet t-shirt contests, even basketball courts on the beach.

properties.name: San Diego Zoo
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27San Diego, CAAlmost everyone likes animals. Well San Diego Zoo is arguable the best place in the United States to see about every kind of animal imaginable, almost in their natural habitat. They even have a safari ride where you get to see lions, giraffes, elephants and much more in a simulated natural environment.

properties.name: Santa Fe
properties.description: Posted by Dtaylo27Santa Fe, NMDeserts, Humongous rocks, Rocky Mountains in the distance, and Indian Reservations. All kinds of cool pottery, cool indian dances, pretty awesome.
